        <div n="676-ROGP" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-1"> That you, friend Marcus, like a Stoic,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-2"> Can wish to die, in strain heroic,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-3"> No real fortitude implies:</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-4"> Yet, all must own, thy wish is wise.</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="5" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-5">Thy curate's place, thy fruitful wife,&#13;</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-6"> Thy busy, drudging scene of life,</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-7"> Thy insolent illiterate vicar,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-8"> Thy want of all-consoling liquor,</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-9"> Thy threadbare gown, thy cassock rent,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-10"> Thy credit sunk, thy money spent,</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-11"> Thy week made up of fasting days,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-12"> Thy grate unconscious of a blaze,<gap/><gap/><gap/><gap/></l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-13"> And, to complete thy other curses,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-14"> The quarterly demand of nurses,</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-15"> Are ills you wisely wish to leave,</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-16"> And fly for refuge to the grave:</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-17"> And, O what virtue you express</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-18"> In wishing such afflictions less!</l></lg><lg n="3" type="stanza"><l n="19" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-19">But, now should fortune shift the scene,&#13;</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-20"> And make thy curateship a dean;</l><l n="21" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-21"> Or some rich benefice provide,</l><l n="22" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-22"> To pamper luxury and pride;</l><l n="23" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-23"> With labour small, and income great;</l><l n="24" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-24"> With chariot less for use than state;</l><l n="25" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-25"> With swelling scarf, and glossy gown,</l><l n="26" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-26"> And licence to reside in town;</l><l n="27" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-27"> To shine, where all the gay resort,</l><l n="28" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-28"> At concert, coffee-house, or court;</l><l n="29" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-29"> And weekly persecute his Grace</l><l n="30" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-30"> With visits, or to beg a place;</l><l n="31" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-31"> With underlings thy flocks to teach,</l><l n="32" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-32"> With no desire to pray or preach;</l><l n="33" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-33"> With haughty spouse in vesture fine,</l><l n="34" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-34"> With plenteous meals, and generous wine;</l><l n="35" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-35"> Wouldst thou not wish, in so much ease,</l><l n="36" xml:id="spp-676-ROGP-line-36"> Thy years as numerous as thy days?676-ROGP   </l></lg></div>
